The paper focuses on the evolution of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also applies the evolutionary process to the task of visual saliency, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the modeling capabilities of the evolved networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of computational environmental factor models, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
